Your Honour,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I deeply regret the actions that led to this incident and take full responsibility for my reckless behavior.

On the day in question, I was in a rush to get to the airport to pick up my family members. In my haste, I made poor decisions by driving aggressively and exceeding the speed limit. Additionally, I made the grave mistake of answering a text message while behind the wheel. These irresponsible actions resulted in a collision with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was harmed in this incident.

I am fully aware of the dangers my actions posed and the potential harm that could have been caused to myself and others on the road. Reflecting on this incident, I now understand the severity of my behavior and the potential consequences that could have unfolded.

In terms of my involvement, I am a 37-year-old individual with an otherwise clean record. I take pride in abiding by the law and ensuring the safety of myself and others. I have been actively involved in supporting charitable causes, particularly the British Heart Foundation, where I regularly make donations. I believe this showcases my commitment to being a responsible citizen and contributing positively to society.

Although I understand that my actions on that day were inexcusable, I want to assure the court that this incident was an isolated lapse in judgment. I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience and am truly remorseful for the potential harm I could have caused.

In conclusion, Your Honour, I plead guilty to careless driving and accept the consequences that come with it. I humbly request a fair and just disposition, taking into consideration my clean record, genuine remorse, and commitment to making amends for my actions. I assure the court that I have taken steps to rectify my behavior and prevent any future recurrence of such an incident.

Thank you for your attention to this matter.

Sincerely,
Charlotte Porter

