I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of careless driving. I understand the gravity of my actions and fully accept responsibility for the reckless behavior that resulted in this unfortunate incident.

On the day in question, I was in a hurry to pick up my family members from the airport. However, instead of making responsible choices, I allowed my impatience to cloud my judgment. I drove aggressively, exceeding the speed limit, and even succumbed to the temptation of checking a text message while behind the wheel. As a consequence of my negligence, I collided with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was injured.

