In light of this, I want to emphasize that this incident does not define who I am as a person. I am 37 years old, and up until this point, I have maintained a clean record. Furthermore, I am an active supporter of the British Heart Foundation, regularly donating to their cause. My involvement with this organization reflects my genuine concern for the welfare of others.

In conclusion, Your Honour, I express my sincere remorse for my careless driving and the potential harm it could have caused. I am here today to accept the consequences of my actions and to assure the court that I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience. I am committed to becoming a more responsible and conscientious driver moving forward.

Thank you for your attention and understanding.

