I stand before you today to admit my guilt for the charge of careless driving. I deeply regret the choices I made on that day, which led to the unfortunate collision with a guardrail.

On the day of the incident, I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members. In my haste, I drove aggressively, exceeding the speed limit, and made the irresponsible decision to answer a text message from my cousin while behind the wheel. As a result of these actions, I lost control of my vehicle and crashed into a guardrail.

I now realize the extreme danger I put myself and others in by engaging in such reckless behavior. Looking back, I am fully aware of the potential harm that could have been caused not just to myself but to innocent individuals sharing the road with me.

I would like to bring your attention to the fact that I am a 37-year-old individual with an otherwise clean driving record. I hold myself to a high standard of responsibility and safety on the road. Furthermore, I am an active supporter of the British Heart Foundation, demonstrating my commitment to the well-being of others.

With sincere remorse, I acknowledge the severity of my actions and I am prepared to face the consequences. I want to assure the court that this incident is out of character for me and does not reflect the person I strive to be. I have taken this experience as a valuable lesson and commit to becoming a more responsible and considerate driver.

Thank you for your consideration and understanding.

Sincerely,
Charlotte Porter

