Your Honour,

I am appearing before you today to take full responsibility for the charge of careless driving. I deeply regret my actions that led to the collision with a guardrail.

Upon reflection, I now understand the magnitude of the danger I caused not only to myself but to others on the road. On that day, I was rushing to pick up my family members from the airport, and in my haste, I drove aggressively, exceeded the speed limit, and even answered a text message from my cousin.

I want to emphasize that my guilty plea reflects my sincere acknowledgment of my wrongdoing and my commitment to being accountable for my actions. I believe this should be taken into consideration as a mitigating factor. I have 3 penalty points for speeding on my licence already, which I acknowledge as evidence of my previous traffic violation.

I am fully aware of the gravity of the situation and the consequences of my actions. I have learned an invaluable lesson from this experience and now understand the importance of responsible decision-making while driving.

I appear before you today with genuine remorse for my actions. I respectfully request your comprehension and fair judgment in this matter, considering my guilty plea as a sign of my willingness to accept the consequences of my choices.

Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely,
Charlotte Porter
